{"questionId":"23665221","questionHtml":"<p>The binomial expansion of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>n</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℚ</mi></math>.</em></p>\n<p>Find the value of <em>n</em>&nbsp;and the value of <em>k</em>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to apply binomial expansion&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em>&nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><msup><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></msup><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi><msup><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></msup><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mrow></mrow><mi>n</mi></msup><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mrow></mrow><mi>n</mi></msup><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong> &nbsp;<em> (A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>!</mo></mrow><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>!</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>!</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em>&nbsp; <strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn></math></p>\n<p>valid attempt to solve&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; finding correct value in Pascal’s triangle</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>Note:</strong> If candidate finds&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;with no working shown, award <em><strong>M1A0A0M1A1A0</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">If candidate finds&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>with no working shown, award <em><strong>M1A0A0M1A1A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[6 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"23665221","referenceCode":"23N.1.SL.TZ1.6","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"The binomial expansion of 1+kxn is given by 1+9x2+15k2x2+…+knxn, where n∈ℤ+ and k∈ℚ. Find the value of n and the value of k.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"6","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.9—Binomial theorem where n is an integer"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}